`logv --match -s 'Start (\w)' -e 'End (\w)'`
Accepts regexp for start and end with one group (maybe 
named KEY). Prints matched and non-matched lines:
```
Matched: key/line1 #/line2 #
Non-matched: key/line
```</markdown><markdown id="markdown5" x="112px" y="1043px" width="auto" height="auto" fontSize="16px">**Search**

`Ctrl+F` - regular search. `F3`/`Shift+F3` next/prev match
`Shift+Ctrl+f` - search report (like Find all occurrences in Notepad++) 
Accepts regexp</markdown><markdown id="markdown6" x="130px" y="301px" width="auto" height="auto" fontSize="16px">**Status Bar**

FQ File name, Size, Cursor Offset</markdown><markdown id="markdown7" x="771px" y="1240px" width="auto" height="auto" fontSize="16px"><![CDATA[**SSH**

Remote file reader

